  </div>

  <header class="entry-header">
    <h1 class="entry-title" itemprop="name headline">Rohingya refugee boy works to support family</h1>

    <div class="entry-meta">
      <div class="entry-meta-top">
        <span class="location entry-location">
          <a class="location-icon" href="http://maps.google.com/maps?q=21.439464,92.007732" target="_blank"></a>           Cox's Bazar, <a href="/country/bangladesh">Bangladesh</a>
        </span>

          
            
              <span class="entry-authors">
          <span class="entry-author" itemscope itemprop="author" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
            <a itemprop="url" href="/photographer/adnan-abidi">
              <img class="entry-author-pic" itemprop="image" src="https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/f0ofMhO1fOI2212VopfhoMJoNG8FT3QEV-Ll4gd2KshjzFCMhX1EydCInZvoCbqrWrcmq5E1DlzSCJWsVRla0A" alt="Adnan Abidi" />
              <span class="entry-author-name" itemprop="name">Adnan Abidi</span>
            </a>
          </span>
        </span>
          
    
  
  



      </div>

      <div class="entry-meta-bot">
        <time class="entry-date">Updated 13 Nov 2017</time>
        <span class="entry-imagesnumber">21 images</span>

        
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="entry-content">

    <div class="entry-ad">
      <span>Advertisement</span>
      <div class="entry-ad-wrapper">
          <div id="ad-story-leaderboard"></div>
      </div>
    </div>

          <p class="wrap">Twelve-year-old Nur Hafes would rather be in school or playing football with friends at home in Myanmar.</p>
          <p class="wrap">Instead, he waits by the road in Palong Khali refugee camp in southern Bangladesh, looking for visitors who might give him money for his family.</p>
    

                  <figure class="widget widget-image widget-image-large-center">
  <div class="image-wrapper">
          <img sizes="(min-width: 500px) 100vw, 50vw" srcset="https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/dqXP9WC0Q5E0WCSnUdU6DRkYUN7BffZuLaiTwHD8eSD3n1jRj4Ic271IDABMtOLStLj0RlVwRQvs2qq5lHFB5Q 480w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/JriyrsiwoBOmJqrlYRQaSubnNDisaAStXZJ-A_P3d87WvUwuzkXCf8V4HT2YCL4U3fAm8vi3tkEoMTVLtU7p2Q 768w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/e9hyHkaRFZdDV_jLZuTS6r5bp9ENzH6awVUWotB22s0x6OJaG8G3OG7bcjTMAN14nochyfxpS5pOHVdWTKzdxQ 1230w" alt="" />
                <figcaption class="figure-meta">
      <time>30 Oct 2017</time>. Cox's Bazar, Bangladesh. Reuters/Adnan Abidi
    </figcaption>
    <span class="image-info"></span>
  </div>
    <div class="widget-content">
    <div class="wrap">
                    <p>Sole breadwinner for seven younger siblings and his mother since they arrived at the camp in Cox&#039;s Bazar two months ago, Nur (left) spends his days watching for Muslim clerics who distribute money collected at mosques for the refugees.</p>
              <p>Opening a brown umbrella, Nur offers to shade the visitors from the blazing sun, which can bring in a little extra cash for food and supplies.</p>
      
    </div>
  </div>
</figure>
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
                        <figure class="widget widget-image widget-image-large-center">
  <div class="image-wrapper">
          <img sizes="(min-width: 500px) 100vw, 50vw" srcset="https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/dqXP9WC0Q5E0WCSnUdU6DZ789rdP7ZHtKKuqKPvk82XYELG2r7A5eSAkzahynrZfggy57CQ4QsMLEi9Xo7lXCA 480w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/JriyrsiwoBOmJqrlYRQaSm1yqRDwxfZmfdBxPd5n2qmEUC4xI7r3ZIj8O2NhsVZ-rcyy-do0bavCihRsKfGFQQ 768w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/e9hyHkaRFZdDV_jLZuTS6kmw2lyVtkPrdktzXYvAaI4o8jY298xpD2Xzdyydd-lWvCF1YUyCyso6L_KXCqgpTg 1230w" alt="" />
                <figcaption class="figure-meta">
      <time>27 Oct 2017</time>. Cox's Bazar, Bangladesh. Reuters/Adnan Abidi
    </figcaption>
    <span class="image-info"></span>
  </div>
    <div class="widget-content">
    <div class="wrap">
                    <p>&quot;Sometimes I get 50 or 100 taka and some days I come back empty-handed,&quot; Nur said, holding up a 50-taka ($0.60) note he received from a donor.</p>
              <p>Nur and his family are among the more than 600,000 Rohingyas who have fled to Bangladesh since August to escape a counter-insurgency operation by the Myanmar military after attacks on security posts by Rohingya militants.</p>
      
    </div>
  </div>
</figure>
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
                
