              <div class="wrap">
  <h3 class="is-hidden">Story</h3>
  
      
<p>United Nations officials have described the military's actions in Myanmar's northern Rakhine state as "ethnic cleansing", an accusation the Southeast Asian nation denies.</p><p>The family left their home in Tharay Kone Yoe Dan village in Rakhine's Maungdaw township when the violence started.</p>
  
  </div>

      
      
      
      
      
      
                        <figure class="widget widget-image widget-image-large-center">
  <div class="image-wrapper">
          <img sizes="(min-width: 500px) 100vw, 50vw" srcset="https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/dqXP9WC0Q5E0WCSnUdU6DduIucselsZJHcYap2aXRFzhSw7I0WeC2w9Sl0EjG1crbe2dv8MTYcz5_l_C4heS2A 480w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/JriyrsiwoBOmJqrlYRQaSpGDQV2ZqdBDuX3IfroZwSicymkfwO4IAWFngzZxl7qAlkmxQvHkNi9ROJmUr0HdQA 768w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/e9hyHkaRFZdDV_jLZuTS6manDsUZa-DqkfPprkf5GArQfFCwKtvJGng8pOZv_jwTA-NmYcSJRYQw2TvblVVqLA 1230w" alt="" />
                <figcaption class="figure-meta">
      <time>27 Oct 2017</time>. Cox's Bazar, Bangladesh. Reuters/Adnan Abidi
    </figcaption>
    <span class="image-info"></span>
  </div>
    <div class="widget-content">
    <div class="wrap">
                    <p>&quot;The Myanmar army burnt the houses with the people inside,&quot; said Nur&#039;s mother, Rabia Khatun.</p>
              <p>&quot;I saw many people with gunshot wounds and heard the crackle of houses burning.&quot;</p>
      
    </div>
  </div>
</figure>
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
                        <figure class="widget widget-image widget-image-large-center">
  <div class="image-wrapper">
          <img sizes="(min-width: 500px) 100vw, 50vw" srcset="https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/dqXP9WC0Q5E0WCSnUdU6DWIOcp1t1NuswITTyhZbti8Xv5hcPcP-rRCuYsx-hLQVQ0tgXBoYyquq9OQpeHyWRw 480w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/JriyrsiwoBOmJqrlYRQaSmhdhn6NSGRfvIy3a7R5ZCzZBcxm0bg5gMBh0r-2QIjsLTofoHj0kgBvuAQ_zoU6iA 768w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/e9hyHkaRFZdDV_jLZuTS6tqFsLQjYddAemgJ2FJp-8EIr2kEJH92srYBx6ipmhdeOyhuc1xuUJfQwEICE-MPDQ 1230w" alt="" />
                <figcaption class="figure-meta">
      <time>29 Oct 2017</time>. Cox's Bazar, Bangladesh. Reuters/Adnan Abidi
    </figcaption>
    <span class="image-info"></span>
  </div>
    <div class="widget-content">
    <div class="wrap">
                    <p>She gathered a few belongings - a blanket to protect her children from rain, identity papers and a couple of old photos - and the family fled to her parents&#039; village, Zaw Mat Tat, south of Maungdaw.</p>
              <p>The next day, the army showed up there, too. Her husband became upset and suddenly left. Rabia has not seen him since.</p>
      
    </div>
  </div>
</figure>
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
                        <figure class="widget widget-image widget-image-large-center">
  <div class="image-wrapper">
          <img sizes="(min-width: 500px) 100vw, 50vw" srcset="https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/dqXP9WC0Q5E0WCSnUdU6DeBDW_kNAxDzgjNAfgWyuu_7FuR0bVtihc7jeLy_PpZJm1k4IxYo181gtoKJwWgr9w 480w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/JriyrsiwoBOmJqrlYRQaSq7qMM2Dn8JvKlCvkGziEOxazTE4JJTkxRtl7cHJa4jpmfiNQDuuqmP0PKrf9f2u2w 768w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/e9hyHkaRFZdDV_jLZuTS6v1kjFUvoSIfwqlYWH3Suebo9vF736laZTq70HjThWy1PhKYbFWN-IFqkiVy4uOTOg 1230w" alt="" />
                <figcaption class="figure-meta">
      <time>27 Oct 2017</time>. Cox's Bazar, Bangladesh. Reuters/Adnan Abidi
    </figcaption>
    <span class="image-info"></span>
  </div>
    <div class="widget-content">
    <div class="wrap">
                    <p>Left with eight children, six of them younger than 10, she kept going. That evening, the family took a three-hour boat journey to Shah Porir Dwip, on the Bangladesh side of the Naf River.</p>
              <p>Now the family relies on Nur for support. He was a huge help in Myanmar, reselling produce in their village market that his father had bought wholesale.</p>
      
    </div>
  </div>
</figure>
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
                        <figure class="widget widget-image widget-image-large-center">
  <div class="image-wrapper">
          <img sizes="(min-width: 500px) 100vw, 50vw" srcset="https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/dqXP9WC0Q5E0WCSnUdU6DdDZ6e2UY6W777c7bfV1_gbnTybAixA3-fObK_QcyR34H-miBaxuDtLHtaJM1Y4xxg 480w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/JriyrsiwoBOmJqrlYRQaSpN64ubTZ3Ui3_Z06n4xlQEjk4Wwp_Uu_DXhvhv97DKyXW7yK1RYDnxc9S3ZKg7d7w 768w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/e9hyHkaRFZdDV_jLZuTS6vOgPcCBD_-EyZrfFZsTaJIkkxBgLteb5VdDjshMkFS4wiYVYku9vTSnXqSRRfxUHw 1230w" alt="" />
                <figcaption class="figure-meta">
      <time>3 Nov 2017</time>. Cox's Bazar, Bangladesh. Reuters/Adnan Abidi
    </figcaption>
    <span class="image-info"></span>
  </div>
    <div class="widget-content">
    <div class="wrap">
                    <p>Nur and his mother said they hope he can eventually do something similar in Bangladesh, although Nur also still talks about school and football.</p>
      
    </div>
  </div>
</figure>
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
                        <figure class="widget widget-image widget-image-large-center">
  <div class="image-wrapper">
          <img sizes="(min-width: 500px) 100vw, 50vw" srcset="https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/dqXP9WC0Q5E0WCSnUdU6DUgtFX3nZaLkk9yK-f6jJHkoUXLa8UFgAjLh35pIV28Zrj2UueOU5uYFhvRceoY97g 480w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/JriyrsiwoBOmJqrlYRQaSpxhbjc75kC76gPqnJVAFR1dbklelHo_xqGM__xZ_RsmLQOltQdsmZDlxJYWf-M42A 768w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/e9hyHkaRFZdDV_jLZuTS6uf35Wgr9rk5mU3398WOQ2vhnDysEbcKRr1O4P_i2silxZfnQ5QhS4crjpY-gfdb3w 1230w" alt="" />
                <figcaption class="figure-meta">
      <time>23 Oct 2017</time>. Cox's Bazar, Bangladesh. Reuters/Adnan Abidi
    </figcaption>
    <span class="image-info"></span>
  </div>
    <div class="widget-content">
    <div class="wrap">
                    <p>With Nur&#039;s family huddled under a tarpaulin tent and his mother needing help to feed his siblings, the youngest two of whom suffer malnourishment, a normal child&#039;s life is not in his immediate future.</p>
              <p>&quot;I know he is young, but he understands his responsibilities. He doesn&#039;t behave like a child any more,&quot; Rabia said.</p>
      
    </div>
  </div>
</figure>
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
                
      
      
      
      
              <div class="wrap">
  <h3 class="is-hidden">Story</h3>
  
      
  
      <p class="story-meta">
      Writing by       Karishma Singh and Tom Hogue
    </p>
  </div>

      
      
      
      
      
      
